description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting vacancy has arisen due to a retirement for a Designated Clinical Officer (DCO) for Special Educational Needs and Disability (SEND).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This interesting and challenging post works with a multitude of organisations with the sole purpose of ensuring our children and young people with SEND receive the health care support they need to thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This requires a high level of relationship building and negotiation skills across all relevant agencies to drive a whole system approach to meeting the needs of our children and young people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will act as a strategic and operational lead for the Education, Health and Care Plan (EHCP) Pathway in accordance with the Children’s and Families Act 2014 as part of a Pan Lancashire Team of three DCO’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is to primarily cover the Pennine Locality although the 3 DCO’s work in collaboration to ensure a consistent approach and to provide cover for each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder works closely with Clinical Commissioning Groups (CCG’s) to ensure they meet their statutory duties for children and young people with SEND aged 0-25 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported by a highly skilled and dedicated administration team who act as a single point of access and coordination for all EHCP requests for health advice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel you have demonstrable experience in delivering against this agenda and the personality and commitment to integrate well, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Lynch  helen.r.lynch@lscft.nhs.uk 07790389171&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anne Hardman DCO on 07973963565 or anne.hardman@lscft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
